						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tomaitheous wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The PCE has Y, R-Y and B-Y and separate CB output pins. Since Cr and Cb aren't summed, all I should have to do with build a four diode bridge rectifier to demodulate each of the two lines. Then apply a light low pass filter.</div>Careful -- you'll need an active rectifier, not a passive one; a conventional 4-diode full-wave rectifier will, even if you use Schottky diodes, drop the center .4V out of your 1Vpp signal.</div>

